<h2>
    <strong>Introduction to Coho Salmon Fishing in the Willamette Valley</strong>
</h2>
<p>
    Coho salmon, also known as "Silver" salmon due to their bright, silvery skin, are a prized catch throughout the Pacific Northwest. They migrate each fall from the ocean into rivers like the Willamette and its tributaries to spawn. Salem, located just an hour from the Oregon Coast, gives anglers quick access to these migration paths.
</p>
<p>
