    </li>
</ul>
<h3>
    <strong>Fly Fishing for Coho in Oregon Waters</strong>
</h3>
<ul>
    <li>
        Use <strong>egg patterns</strong>, <strong>streamers</strong>, or <strong>woolly buggers</strong>.
    </li>
    <li>
        Focus on tailouts and deeper runs where Coho rest.
    </li>
    <li>
        8-weight rods with floating or intermediate lines work well.
    </li>
</ul>
<h3>
    <strong>Drift Fishing and Float Rigs</strong>
</h3>
<ul>
    <li>
